      "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/doocs/leetcode/blob/main/solution/2400-2499/2448.Minimum%20Cost%20to%20Make%20Array%20Equal/README_EN.md",
      "code": "using ll = long long;\n\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    long long minCost(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& cost) {\n        int n = nums.size();\n        vector<pair<int, int>> arr(n);\n        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) arr[i] = {nums[i], cost[i]};\n        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end());\n        ll mid = accumulate(cost.begin(), cost.end(), 0ll) / 2;\n        ll s = 0, ans = 0;\n        for (auto [x, c] : arr) {\n            s += c;\n            if (s > mid) {\n                for (auto [v, d] : arr) {\n                    ans += 1ll * abs(v - x) * d;\n                }\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n};"
